ebated about, summarised and reported but their agency is denied. Each contribution to this volume adds an empirical perspective to our understanding of how language relates to migration in a specific national context. The chapters use innovative combinations of multimodal, qualitative and quantitative analyses to examine a broad range of genres and data related to the voices of migrants and reporting about migrants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aDiscrimination. 0aEmigration and immigrationxGovernment policy. 0aImmigrantsxGovernment policy. 0aImmigrantsxLanguage. 0aLanguage and languagesxPolitical aspects. 0aLanguage policy. 0aSociolinguistics. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aidentity politics.  alanguage and migration.  alanguage policies.  arefugee crisis.  arefugee integration.1 aAngouri, Jo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapstick, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Fina, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOr, Iair G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParaskevaidi, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRheindorf, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRheindorf, Markus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSavski, Kristof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShohamy, Elana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWodak, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWodak, Ruth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZannoni, Federico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTi